# Purpose

Step-by-step procedure for adding a new feature across backend and frontend packages.

# Workflow

## 1. Define Backend Module

Create the module directory: `backend/src/modules/<name>/`

Required files:
- `<name>-controller.ts` — async handler functions
- `<name>-middleware.ts` — Zod-based input validation middleware
- `<name>-routing.ts` — Express Router with rate limiter → middleware → controller chain
- `<name>-registry.ts` — OpenAPI path registration with `@asteasolutions/zod-to-openapi`
- `schemas/` — Zod schemas for request and response
- `types/` — TypeScript types derived from schemas (`z.infer<typeof schema>`)

## 2. Register the Module Router

In `backend/src/server/index.ts` (or the Express app bootstrap), mount the router:

```typescript
import <name>Router from 'modules/<name>/<name>-routing';
app.use(constants.routes.<name>.base, authenticateMiddleware, <name>Router);
```

Add route constants to `shared/constants/routes`.

## 3. Define Repository Methods (if new collection)

In `backend/src/aop/db/mongo/repository/<name>/index.ts`:
- Create repository class extending the pattern from `UserRepository` or `JobsRepository`.
- Validate all returned documents with `parseSchema(schema, doc)`.
- Expose via `req.context.db.repository.<name>`.

## 4. Register in OpenAPI Service

Add the registry to `backend/src/services/openapi` so the spec is generated.

## 5. Regenerate Frontend Types

```bash
cd frontend
npm run generate-types
```

This runs Orval against the backend OpenAPI spec and updates `src/_types/_gen/`.

## 6. Add Frontend API Resource

Create `frontend/src/api/service/resources/<name>/`:
- `index.ts` — functions calling `client.get`, `client.post`, `client.put`, `client.del`
- `config.ts` — path constants
- `types/` — local types if needed beyond `_gen`

Register the resource in `frontend/src/api/index.ts`.

## 7. Add Zustand State (if needed)

Create `frontend/src/store/slices/<name>/`:
- `<name>.state.ts` — initial state shape
- `<name>.types.ts` — `StateCreator` slice type
- `index.ts` — `createXSlice` function

Add selectors to `frontend/src/store/selectors/<name>/`.

## 8. Build Frontend Page/Component

Create `frontend/src/components/pages/<name>/`:
- Page component (default export)
- Sub-components in co-located directories
- Types in `<Component>.types.ts`

Use `ui-app/` components. DO NOT import from `ui/` directly.

## 9. Add Route

Register the route in `frontend/src/config/` and add it to the router in `App.tsx`.

## Validation Commands

```bash
# Backend
cd backend && npm run type-check && npm run lint && npm test

# Frontend
cd frontend && npm run type-check && npm run lint

# Integration
cd backend && npm run test:integration
```

## Completion Criteria

- [ ] Backend module files created with correct naming convention
- [ ] Route constants defined in `shared/constants/routes`
- [ ] Repository validates all reads with `parseSchema`
- [ ] Frontend types regenerated with Orval
- [ ] Frontend API resource functions created
- [ ] `npm run type-check` and `npm run lint` pass in both packages
- [ ] Integration tests added covering HTTP contract
